commit.message:
Update Hybrid Recommender Tutorial

Hi!
I've tried to complete this tutorial and faced some issues due to the discrepancy between lightfm latest version and the one used in the tutorial.

The issue was that checking test AUC score without `check_intersections=False` raises an Exception due to intersected samples.

commit.message:
Add virtualenv setup guide to README

These steps just follow the setup used in CI configuration

Update test command in README

Update this command to run 'pytest', this follows the setup used within
the CI pipelines.

The existing command expects a 'unittest' test suite:
https://setuptools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/setuptools.html#test-build-package-and-run-a-unittest-suite

CI improvements (#541)

* move circle.yml to the default location .circleci/config.yml

* added 2.0/2.1 workflows

* allow restore_cache to restore from multiple keys

* expose test results to CircleCI

* test using multiple python versions

* ignoring non-pep8 compliant E203 error

* fix appveyor reference to requirements

* black-ify setup.py and remove deprecated test command

* update travis osx build to py3
